'''Ada 95''' is the second revision of the language, preceded by [[Ada Programming/Ada 83|Ada 83]]. It was standardized by the [[Wikipedia:International Organization for Standardization|ISO]] in 1995. The Technical Corrigendum 1 was published in June 2001.<ref>{{cite web
 |      title = WG9 Standards and Projects
 |        url = http://www.open-std.org/jtc1/sc22/wg9/projects.htm
 | accessdate = 2008-06-09
 |      quote = The Corrigendum is approved and was published in June 2001.
 }}</ref>

== New language features ==

Main additions:<ref>{{cite web
 |     author = Naomi Hamilton
 |      title = The A-Z of Programming Languages: Ada
 |        url = 2008-06-04
 |  publisher = Computerworld
 |        url = http://www.techworld.com.au/article/223388/-z_programming_languages_ada?pp=1
 | accessdate = 2008-06-09
 |      quote = The "big three" Ada 95 language revisions were Hierarchical Libraries, Protected Objects, and Object-Oriented Programming.
}}</ref>
* [[Ada Programming/Object Orientation|Object Orientation]]
* [[Ada Programming/Tasking#Protected types|Protected Objects]]
* [[Ada Programming/Packages#Child packages|Hierarchical libraries]]

=== Character set ===

* [[Wikipedia:Latin-1|Latin-1]] (8-bit) character set for identifiers
* Type <tt>Character</tt> expanded to the 256 values of Latin-1 (8 bits)
* New type <tt>Wide_Character</tt> (16-bit character type, [[w:UCS-2|UCS-2]] encoding) and <tt>Wide_String</tt>

=== Specialized Needs Annexes ===

* Annex C, "Systems Programming"
* Annex D, "Real-Time Systems"
* Annex E, "Distributed Systems"
* Annex F, "Information Systems"
* Annex G, "Numerics"
* Annex H, "Safety and Security" (in [[Ada Programming/Ada 2005|Ada 2005]] renamed to "High Integrity Systems")

