{{Ada/Navigation|83}}
__TOC__

'''Ada 83''' is the first version of the [[Wikipedia:Ada (programming language)|Ada programming language]]. It was based in the so called [[Ada Programming/Ada 80|Ada 80]], a preliminary version of the language formally known as MIL-STD-1815 (published in December 1980). This standard was refined and standardized by the [[Wikipedia:United States Department of Defense|DoD]] and [[Wikipedia:American National Standards Institute|ANSI]] as '''ANSI/MIL-STD-1815A''' in February 1983 (note the additional 'A' at the end), which was later adopted by [[Wikipedia:International Organization for Standardization|International Organization for Standardization]] as ISO/IEC 8652:1987.

== Language features ==

=== Character set ===

* Identifiers in ASCII (7-Bit)

